WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:33.199 --> 00:00:35.660 position:50% align:center
[KING]
Yes! I rather like this idea

00:00:35.744 --> 00:00:38.538 position:50% align:center
of an exhibition match
between Azami and Jiou!

00:00:38.621 --> 00:00:40.623 position:50% align:center
What a splendidly
unambiguous way

00:00:40.707 --> 00:00:41.833 position:50% align:center
to show the world
we're committed

00:00:41.916 --> 00:00:44.919 position:50% align:center
to being good neighbors!

00:00:45.003 --> 00:00:47.172 position:50% align:center
In fact, as a sign
of good faith,

00:00:47.255 --> 00:00:50.467 position:50% align:center
we shall send them
our very best warrior.

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:54.179 position:50% align:center
An absolute unit!
Someone fierce! Legendary!

00:00:54.262 --> 00:00:56.014 position:50% align:center
And that would be who?

00:02:31.776 --> 00:02:33.778 position:50% align:center
I'm excited to see
your hometown!

00:02:33.862 --> 00:02:35.822 position:50% align:center
Ha, ha. Manage
your expectations.

00:02:35.905 --> 00:02:37.282 position:50% align:center
Oh, come on.

00:02:37.365 --> 00:02:38.533 position:50% align:center
Hey, why do we have to take

00:02:38.616 --> 00:02:40.910 position:50% align:center
a weird scenic route
like this, chief?

00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:43.997 position:50% align:center
I had intended to use my magic
and teleport us there

00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:45.290 position:50% align:center
in one fell swoop,

00:02:45.373 --> 00:02:47.792 position:50% align:center
but I'm afraid that's
not an option right now.

00:02:47.876 --> 00:02:49.794 position:50% align:center
We have to rendezvous
with a dwarf.

00:02:49.878 --> 00:02:51.629 position:50% align:center
Should be fun.

00:02:51.713 --> 00:02:53.840 position:50% align:center
Kunlun, Kunlun, Kunlun!

00:02:53.923 --> 00:02:56.468 position:50% align:center
Hoards of treasure as
far as the eye can see!

00:02:56.551 --> 00:02:59.763 position:50% align:center
One marriage license form in
my jacket, one in my shirt,

00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:03.058 position:50% align:center
one behind my back,
and one under my skirt!

00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:04.309 position:50% align:center
I am gonna go toe-to-toe

00:03:04.392 --> 00:03:06.269 position:50% align:center
with something
exceptionally tough!

00:03:06.353 --> 00:03:07.645 position:50% align:center
Marriage, here I come!

00:03:07.729 --> 00:03:09.147 position:50% align:center
Treasure, hoard here I come!

00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:10.565 position:50% align:center
Toughness, here I come!

00:03:10.648 --> 00:03:13.526 position:50% align:center
I'll meet Sir Lloyd's family.
Secure their blessing!

00:03:13.610 --> 00:03:18.365 position:50% align:center
Silence! We're going to
Kunlun to restore Vritra!

00:03:18.448 --> 00:03:21.951 position:50% align:center
Not to be a hall monitor, but
should Chrome even be here?

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:23.119 position:50% align:center
I thought the castle had you

00:03:23.203 --> 00:03:25.205 position:50% align:center
drowning in work up
to your sideburns.

00:03:25.288 --> 00:03:27.207 position:50% align:center
Funny you should say that.

00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:31.044 position:50% align:center
[ALAN]
Ahh! Sir Lloyd!

00:03:31.127 --> 00:03:32.128 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:34.005 position:50% align:center
Cast Aqua Whip!

00:03:34.089 --> 00:03:35.965 position:50% align:center
[ALAN groans, sighs]

00:03:36.049 --> 00:03:36.883 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:03:36.966 --> 00:03:39.344 position:50% align:center
Not my first rodeo.

00:03:39.427 --> 00:03:42.347 position:50% align:center
The king wants to see Alan
the Immortal Destroyer.

00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:44.683 position:50% align:center
Consider yourself an
honored guest of the crown

00:03:44.766 --> 00:03:46.309 position:50% align:center
until the exhibition
match is over.

00:03:46.393 --> 00:03:48.937 position:50% align:center
[gasps] He's fighting in
the exhibition match?

00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:50.814 position:50% align:center
That is so unbelievably cool!

00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.399 position:50% align:center
[ALAN]
Is it, though?

00:03:52.482 --> 00:03:54.818 position:50% align:center
[MENA] I've been instructed to
keep you on a very tight leash,

00:03:54.901 --> 00:03:57.153 position:50% align:center
Mister Crimson
Jewel of Darkness.

00:03:57.237 --> 00:03:59.322 position:50% align:center
[ALAN] How many nicknames
are you giving me?

00:03:59.406 --> 00:04:02.158 position:50% align:center
[MENA] Well, that depends on
how many the king makes up.

00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:05.620 position:50% align:center
Why they gotta be so extra?
Do something, Sir Lloyd!

00:04:05.704 --> 00:04:08.039 position:50% align:center
Don't be the guy that
just stands there!

00:04:08.123 --> 00:04:10.291 position:50% align:center
I'm begging you--

00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:12.919 position:50% align:center
[LLOYD] Don't you worry!
I'll be there to cheer you on!

00:04:13.003 --> 00:04:15.755 position:50% align:center
You've totally got this, Alan!

00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:19.634 position:50% align:center
In summation, Mena is more
than capable of covering for me.

00:04:19.718 --> 00:04:21.261 position:50% align:center
[CHOLINE]
Thank you, Mena.

00:04:21.344 --> 00:04:23.513 position:50% align:center
[MARIE]
Best of luck, Alan.

00:04:26.599 --> 00:04:28.893 position:50% align:center
[ALKA]
Here we are.

00:04:28.977 --> 00:04:30.770 position:50% align:center
All right, then.

00:04:32.772 --> 00:04:35.150 position:50% align:center
It's me, Eug! Come on out now!

00:04:41.364 --> 00:04:43.450 position:50% align:center
Greetings and salutations, all!

00:04:43.533 --> 00:04:45.452 position:50% align:center
Professor Eug at your service.

00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:47.328 position:50% align:center
For the record
I'm dwarven royalty,

00:04:47.412 --> 00:04:49.164 position:50% align:center
but no need to make
a big deal out of it.

00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:52.709 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Uhh...

00:04:52.792 --> 00:04:54.919 position:50% align:center
Few more people than
we agreed on, Alk.

00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:57.672 position:50% align:center
Shocking, you've already found
something to complain about.

00:04:57.756 --> 00:04:59.424 position:50% align:center
Is this person really a dwarf?

00:04:59.507 --> 00:05:01.760 position:50% align:center
I'm having more trouble
with the royalty thing.

00:05:01.843 --> 00:05:03.511 position:50% align:center
A boring formality.

00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:06.306 position:50% align:center
Even in my hundies, I've got
the best damn skills of anyone

00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:07.891 position:50% align:center
in the game, and
that's not a game

00:05:07.974 --> 00:05:09.267 position:50% align:center
you're allowed to quit.

00:05:09.351 --> 00:05:10.602 position:50% align:center
Did you say hundies?

00:05:10.685 --> 00:05:12.437 position:50% align:center
In other words, I'm old.

00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:15.273 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Uhh...

00:05:15.357 --> 00:05:18.568 position:50% align:center
Then that must put you around
the same age as the chief.

00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:20.153 position:50% align:center
I'd be very careful
about lumping me

00:05:20.236 --> 00:05:22.322 position:50% align:center
in the same category
as Alka if I were you.

00:05:22.405 --> 00:05:24.949 position:50% align:center
Uh... My bad!
You're nothing alike!

00:05:25.033 --> 00:05:27.452 position:50% align:center
[EUG]
Forgiven. Hey there, Vri.

00:05:27.535 --> 00:05:29.037 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA]
Huh?

00:05:29.120 --> 00:05:30.497 position:50% align:center
What made you think
it'd be a good idea

00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:32.332 position:50% align:center
to go wandering
outside the village?

00:05:32.415 --> 00:05:34.584 position:50% align:center
You've completely derailed
my master plan!

00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:36.378 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA]
It was Alka's fault!

00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:37.712 position:50% align:center
Of course it was Alka's fault!

00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:39.214 position:50% align:center
When is it ever
not Alka's fault?

00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:41.675 position:50% align:center
She's the root of all evil
and the embodiment of idiocy!

00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:43.677 position:50% align:center
How many times have I
told you that as Guardian,

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:45.512 position:50% align:center
it's your job to
bear that in mind?

00:05:45.595 --> 00:05:47.639 position:50% align:center
[ALKA] Excuse me, in case
it slipped your memory,

00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:49.766 position:50% align:center
making an apron out of
his skin was your idea

00:05:49.849 --> 00:05:52.310 position:50% align:center
in the first place! If I'm
the "embodiment of idiocy,"

00:05:52.394 --> 00:05:53.687 position:50% align:center
it's only because
I listened to you

00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:56.690 position:50% align:center
tell me it'd be
a great gift for Lloyd!

00:06:01.069 --> 00:06:03.446 position:50% align:center
Whadd'ya say we put this
behind us and move forward?

00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:05.573 position:50% align:center
Specifically to Kunlun!

00:06:05.657 --> 00:06:08.827 position:50% align:center
[GROUP screams]

00:06:09.828 --> 00:06:11.037 position:50% align:center
Heh.

00:06:15.709 --> 00:06:17.752 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow!

00:06:17.836 --> 00:06:20.714 position:50% align:center
[LLOYD]
Well, there it is!

00:06:22.757 --> 00:06:24.926 position:50% align:center
I've never breathed
air so unsullied.

00:06:25.010 --> 00:06:27.679 position:50% align:center
I pictured something way more
terrifying! This is nice!

00:06:27.762 --> 00:06:28.805 position:50% align:center
And quite tranquil.

00:06:28.888 --> 00:06:31.349 position:50% align:center
Huh. Everything
looks so ordinary.

00:06:31.433 --> 00:06:33.184 position:50% align:center
I thought there'd be
houses made of gold,

00:06:33.268 --> 00:06:36.021 position:50% align:center
or roads paved
with divine artifacts.

00:06:36.104 --> 00:06:38.982 position:50% align:center
Don't let your guard down.
Your eyes might pop out.

00:06:39.065 --> 00:06:41.526 position:50% align:center
What? What does that mean?

00:06:47.157 --> 00:06:51.077 position:50% align:center
[GROUP shivering]

00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:52.662 position:50% align:center
Uh, you guys?

00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:54.372 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I know.

00:06:54.456 --> 00:06:56.666 position:50% align:center
It feels like death is
around every corner!

00:06:56.750 --> 00:06:59.502 position:50% align:center
Why do you all look petrified?

00:06:59.586 --> 00:07:01.755 position:50% align:center
Goodness gracious,
where did I leave it now?

00:07:01.838 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
Oh, upstairs probably!

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.342 position:50% align:center
Or not!

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:08.178 position:50% align:center
[KALOCON]
Hang on. There it is.

00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:09.471 position:50% align:center
[BERRY]
That's what you meant?

00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:11.222 position:50% align:center
[KALOCON] Of course, silly!
Let's get moving.

00:07:11.306 --> 00:07:12.432 position:50% align:center
[BERRY]
Yes, ma'am.

00:07:12.515 --> 00:07:15.268 position:50% align:center
[KENGO] Hang on!
You left the shutters open!

00:07:19.064 --> 00:07:20.732 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:07:20.815 --> 00:07:22.108 position:50% align:center
Yes, yes.

00:07:22.192 --> 00:07:23.943 position:50% align:center
"Sorry, I had to see
about some business.

00:07:24.027 --> 00:07:25.528 position:50% align:center
Should be back in an hour or so!

00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:27.781 position:50% align:center
Would you mind
making lunch, please?"

00:07:27.864 --> 00:07:31.201 position:50% align:center
"I'll make your
favorite, stewed yams!"

00:07:31.284 --> 00:07:33.536 position:50% align:center
There we go.

00:07:38.041 --> 00:07:40.585 position:50% align:center
Well, bit wide of the mark,
but what can you do?

00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:43.672 position:50% align:center
Old age is finally
creepin' up on me.

00:07:43.755 --> 00:07:45.799 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
What in the actual--

00:07:45.882 --> 00:07:49.594 position:50% align:center
Uh. That's, uh, how we
country folk talk long distance.

00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:51.805 position:50% align:center
As I live and breathe,
is that Lloyd?

00:07:51.888 --> 00:07:54.391 position:50% align:center
Hi Mrs. Locomo,
it's good to be back!

00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:55.809 position:50% align:center
[LOCOMO]
Good to see you!

00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:57.477 position:50% align:center
Thanks!

00:07:58.269 --> 00:08:00.814 position:50% align:center
[GLUCO]
Hey, Locomo!

00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:02.524 position:50% align:center
Do me a favor
and pack this thing

00:08:02.607 --> 00:08:05.110 position:50% align:center
with some magic stones
and what not, will ya?

00:08:05.193 --> 00:08:08.279 position:50% align:center
[LOCOMO]
Yeah, yeah! Give me a moment!

00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:09.739 position:50% align:center
Blast me, mama!

00:08:09.823 --> 00:08:11.616 position:50% align:center
[LOCOMO grunts]

00:08:13.451 --> 00:08:16.246 position:50% align:center
[GROUP screaming]

00:08:16.329 --> 00:08:17.747 position:50% align:center
Darn it, he fell short!

00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:20.458 position:50% align:center
Shoulda ground a few more magic
stones in with the powder.

00:08:20.542 --> 00:08:23.712 position:50% align:center
My technique just isn't as sharp
as it was in the old days.

00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:24.963 position:50% align:center
What did we just see?

00:08:25.046 --> 00:08:27.298 position:50% align:center
Is that man alive or what?

00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:29.300 position:50% align:center
Oh, sometimes when
we're in a rush

00:08:29.384 --> 00:08:31.678 position:50% align:center
to get somewhere,
it's easier to fly. No big.

00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:33.013 position:50% align:center
Sucks when we miss the target,

00:08:33.096 --> 00:08:35.640 position:50% align:center
but otherwise pretty
efficient mode of travel.

00:08:35.724 --> 00:08:38.518 position:50% align:center
I retract what I said
about this place being ordinary.

00:08:38.601 --> 00:08:42.480 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Feels like we've wandered
onto a battleground.

00:08:43.773 --> 00:08:44.941 position:50% align:center
Do you see what I see?

00:08:45.025 --> 00:08:46.651 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh! That's a killer piranha!

00:08:46.735 --> 00:08:47.944 position:50% align:center
[LLOYD]
Gramps!

00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:50.822 position:50% align:center
Oh-ho! Lloyd! Is that you?

00:08:50.905 --> 00:08:51.823 position:50% align:center
I've come home!

00:08:51.906 --> 00:08:52.991 position:50% align:center
[PYRID]
Welcome back!

00:08:53.074 --> 00:08:53.950 position:50% align:center
Is that...?

00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:56.661 position:50% align:center
[PYRID chuckles]

00:08:56.745 --> 00:08:58.788 position:50% align:center
May I help you, young lady?

00:08:58.872 --> 00:09:00.874 position:50% align:center
You are Pyrid the
Ogre Lord, are you not?

00:09:00.957 --> 00:09:03.168 position:50% align:center
Teach me your ways,
o' legendary one!

00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:06.087 position:50% align:center
Hey, now! You're using a
stance from my fighting style!

00:09:06.171 --> 00:09:08.131 position:50% align:center
Yeah! She's been studying you!

00:09:08.214 --> 00:09:10.258 position:50% align:center
Turns out Phyllo's a huge fan!

00:09:10.342 --> 00:09:11.634 position:50% align:center
[PYRID]
Ooh!

00:09:11.718 --> 00:09:14.387 position:50% align:center
Yes. With all respect,
I practice the Pyrid Style.

00:09:14.471 --> 00:09:17.098 position:50% align:center
Heh! I can't recall the last
time I've seen that stance

00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:19.559 position:50% align:center
outside of a daily
warm-up routine.

00:09:19.642 --> 00:09:20.894 position:50% align:center
Sorry, what?

00:09:20.977 --> 00:09:23.646 position:50% align:center
Yup! The whole village
does Pyrid Style!

00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:28.068 position:50% align:center
[PYRID] Feel the burn!
One, two! One, two!

00:09:28.151 --> 00:09:29.235 position:50% align:center
[PHYLLO screams]

00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.446 position:50% align:center
And her soul just
left her body.

00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:35.033 position:50% align:center
Welp, I guess one person's MMA
is someone else's Pilates.

00:09:35.116 --> 00:09:37.577 position:50% align:center
[laughs] What the hay,
it's been a while,

00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:40.497 position:50% align:center
I don't see the harm in
showing you a thing or two.

00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:41.956 position:50% align:center
[CHROME chuckles]

00:09:42.040 --> 00:09:43.875 position:50% align:center
Just let me find something
to do with this fish first.

00:09:43.958 --> 00:09:46.628 position:50% align:center
[RIHO] Oh! Me, me, me, me!
I'll hold onto it for you!

00:09:46.711 --> 00:09:48.505 position:50% align:center
[PYRID chuckles]
Well aren't you considerate.

00:09:48.588 --> 00:09:49.756 position:50% align:center
Sure! Least I could do.

00:09:49.839 --> 00:09:51.716 position:50% align:center
[PYRID]
Thank you very much!

00:09:51.800 --> 00:09:53.718 position:50% align:center
Uh! No worries.
I can handle this!

00:09:53.802 --> 00:09:55.095 position:50% align:center
[PYRID]
Atta girl!

00:09:56.346 --> 00:09:58.932 position:50% align:center
[ALKA]
This is my humble abode.

00:10:03.269 --> 00:10:05.313 position:50% align:center
Excuse me, Alka,
but could you point me

00:10:05.397 --> 00:10:06.898 position:50% align:center
in the direction of
you-know-who?

00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:08.775 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Of course. Yes.

00:10:08.858 --> 00:10:11.736 position:50% align:center
I forget, he's the whole
reason you two came along!

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:16.199 position:50% align:center
I believe you'll find him out
back in the wheat fields.

00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:17.992 position:50% align:center
Thank you!

00:10:21.579 --> 00:10:23.373 position:50% align:center
That's so cute.

00:10:31.423 --> 00:10:34.759 position:50% align:center
Merthophan! It's really you!

00:10:34.843 --> 00:10:36.386 position:50% align:center
[MERTHOPHAN]
That voice...

00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:37.804 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:44.686 position:50% align:center
[BOTH grunt]

00:10:44.769 --> 00:10:47.480 position:50% align:center
Hey, guys. How's it goin'?

00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:51.776 position:50% align:center
[MERTHOPHAN]
I'm surprised to see you here.

00:10:51.860 --> 00:10:53.194 position:50% align:center
How long has it been?

00:10:53.278 --> 00:10:54.487 position:50% align:center
[CHROME]
Not quite long enough for us

00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:56.364 position:50% align:center
to process your
new fashion sense.

00:10:56.448 --> 00:10:57.866 position:50% align:center
Huh? What are you talking about?

00:10:57.949 --> 00:11:00.744 position:50% align:center
I love this outfit.
It's very traditional.

00:11:00.827 --> 00:11:01.953 position:50% align:center
[CHOLINE grunting]

00:11:02.037 --> 00:11:04.164 position:50% align:center
[MERTHOPHAN]
Hm? Something wrong, Choline?

00:11:04.247 --> 00:11:05.957 position:50% align:center
Seems like you're
rather quiet today.

00:11:06.041 --> 00:11:06.833 position:50% align:center
[CHOLINE]
No, I--

00:11:06.916 --> 00:11:08.001 position:50% align:center
Ah! Where are my manners?

00:11:08.084 --> 00:11:10.211 position:50% align:center
No clue why it took me
so long to notice.

00:11:10.295 --> 00:11:12.213 position:50% align:center
Whatever could you
be referring to?

00:11:12.297 --> 00:11:13.423 position:50% align:center
Don't be ashamed.

00:11:13.506 --> 00:11:14.883 position:50% align:center
We all have to relieve
ourselves every now

00:11:14.966 --> 00:11:16.801 position:50% align:center
and then throughout
the course of a given day.

00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:18.720 position:50% align:center
You may do your business
in the fields.

00:11:18.803 --> 00:11:19.971 position:50% align:center
Matter of fact, I'm grateful

00:11:20.055 --> 00:11:21.848 position:50% align:center
for the offering
of fresh fertilizer.

00:11:21.931 --> 00:11:22.807 position:50% align:center
Though crops here are self--

00:11:22.891 --> 00:11:24.601 position:50% align:center
[CHOLINE]
Idiot!

00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:29.689 position:50% align:center
Some things never change.
He just swapped out patriotism

00:11:29.773 --> 00:11:31.566 position:50% align:center
for an obsession
with agriculture.

00:11:31.649 --> 00:11:34.277 position:50% align:center
You gotta learn to read
the room sometime, pal.

00:11:34.361 --> 00:11:35.862 position:50% align:center
I will have you know
that my passion

00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:37.405 position:50% align:center
for human feces stems
from it being

00:11:37.489 --> 00:11:40.450 position:50% align:center
one of the most nutrient rich
fertilizers in existence--!

00:11:40.533 --> 00:11:42.452 position:50% align:center
Stop talking, please!

00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:43.995 position:50% align:center
[CHROME sputtering]

00:11:44.079 --> 00:11:48.166 position:50% align:center
[CHOLINE] How did I fall for
someone with such a gross kink?

00:11:48.249 --> 00:11:49.584 position:50% align:center
[CHROME] When do you
plan on being done here

00:11:49.668 --> 00:11:52.045 position:50% align:center
and returning to Azami?

00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:54.130 position:50% align:center
Well, actually--

00:11:54.214 --> 00:11:56.174 position:50% align:center
Though I may have
only been a pawn,

00:11:56.257 --> 00:11:59.427 position:50% align:center
nonetheless I still took part
in attempting a coup.

00:11:59.511 --> 00:12:01.846 position:50% align:center
I'm an outlaw.

00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:05.433 position:50% align:center
Besides, I've grown
fond of this place.

00:12:05.517 --> 00:12:07.310 position:50% align:center
Farming is good for me.

00:12:07.394 --> 00:12:10.939 position:50% align:center
The more work I put in,
the more I get out of it.

00:12:11.022 --> 00:12:12.440 position:50% align:center
[CHROME]
Not unlike the cadets.

00:12:12.524 --> 00:12:14.275 position:50% align:center
[MERTHOPHAN]
Crops are more straightforward,

00:12:14.359 --> 00:12:17.153 position:50% align:center
but I do miss the
Academy sometimes.

00:12:19.739 --> 00:12:23.326 position:50% align:center
All the same, I can't go back.

00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:25.912 position:50% align:center
I'm needed. Here, I mean.

00:12:25.995 --> 00:12:28.581 position:50% align:center
Every single plant
is a responsibility.

00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.458 position:50% align:center
They're like my children.

00:12:30.542 --> 00:12:32.627 position:50% align:center
[CHROME]
That's very admirable.

00:12:34.796 --> 00:12:36.214 position:50% align:center
So, how've you been, Lloyd?

00:12:36.297 --> 00:12:38.216 position:50% align:center
It's good to have you
back here in Kunlun.

00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:40.593 position:50% align:center
Mr. Gorei! How are you?
And Cumin!

00:12:40.677 --> 00:12:42.012 position:50% align:center
It's good to see you, too!

00:12:42.095 --> 00:12:43.263 position:50% align:center
[GROUP chattering]

00:12:43.346 --> 00:12:45.140 position:50% align:center
[SELEN] Surely those are
Sir Lloyd's relatives.

00:12:45.223 --> 00:12:48.059 position:50% align:center
I must make a
formal introduction!

00:12:48.143 --> 00:12:49.936 position:50% align:center
[SELEN]
Greetings, all.

00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:52.689 position:50% align:center
My name is Selen Hemein,
at your service.

00:12:52.772 --> 00:12:54.274 position:50% align:center
Please, honor me
with your acquaintance

00:12:54.357 --> 00:12:57.110 position:50% align:center
and I shall hold it
as a blessing!

00:12:57.193 --> 00:12:58.486 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:01.114 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:13:01.197 --> 00:13:02.741 position:50% align:center
I have taken the liberty
of filling in

00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:04.034 position:50% align:center
all the required fields.

00:13:04.117 --> 00:13:05.326 position:50% align:center
[SOFRA]
What is this?

00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:07.954 position:50% align:center
All I can make sense
of is Lloyd's name.

00:13:08.038 --> 00:13:09.914 position:50% align:center
[SELEN]
Grovel for a signature.

00:13:09.998 --> 00:13:13.001 position:50% align:center
It's my desire
to marry Sir Lloyd.

00:13:13.084 --> 00:13:14.044 position:50% align:center
[thuds]

00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:15.670 position:50% align:center
What is the infernal noise?

00:13:15.754 --> 00:13:18.006 position:50% align:center
Not again. Such a pest.

00:13:18.089 --> 00:13:21.634 position:50% align:center
Hold it! Come any closer and
I'll crush you! Do not test me!

00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:23.345 position:50% align:center
Hey! It's the flying lizard!

00:13:23.428 --> 00:13:26.765 position:50% align:center
As in, like,
a super rare monster?

00:13:26.848 --> 00:13:28.558 position:50% align:center
[thuds continue]

00:13:28.641 --> 00:13:31.478 position:50% align:center
I really ought to run
that thing off for good.

00:13:31.561 --> 00:13:32.937 position:50% align:center
[RIHO] Know what?
Let me take care of it!

00:13:33.021 --> 00:13:34.397 position:50% align:center
Sure. Okay.

00:13:34.481 --> 00:13:35.690 position:50% align:center
[DRAGON A]
Hm?

00:13:35.774 --> 00:13:37.567 position:50% align:center
[roars]

00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.361 position:50% align:center
That's more than
a flying lizard!

00:13:39.444 --> 00:13:40.487 position:50% align:center
[DRAGON A grunts]

00:13:40.570 --> 00:13:43.490 position:50% align:center
[RIHO]
No!

00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:47.285 position:50% align:center
You stay away from me! [cries]

00:13:47.369 --> 00:13:48.286 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:13:48.370 --> 00:13:50.622 position:50% align:center
[RIHO screams]

00:13:50.705 --> 00:13:52.040 position:50% align:center
Nice throw there, Berry!

00:13:52.123 --> 00:13:53.166 position:50% align:center
I've only just started!

00:13:53.249 --> 00:13:54.376 position:50% align:center
[BERRY, CUMIN]
Take that! And that!

00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:57.712 position:50% align:center
And that! Shoo! Yay! We did it!

00:13:57.796 --> 00:13:59.130 position:50% align:center
[BERRY]
I call dibs on the horn!

00:13:59.214 --> 00:14:00.548 position:50% align:center
[CUMIN]
Hey, no fair!

00:14:00.632 --> 00:14:02.175 position:50% align:center
[BERRY]
I made the first shot!

00:14:02.258 --> 00:14:03.885 position:50% align:center
[SELEN]
So much for securing a fortune

00:14:03.968 --> 00:14:05.428 position:50% align:center
beyond your wildest dreams.

00:14:05.512 --> 00:14:08.056 position:50% align:center
You're no closer to getting
what you want than I am.

00:14:08.139 --> 00:14:09.265 position:50% align:center
[SELEN]
Hm?

00:14:09.349 --> 00:14:11.142 position:50% align:center
Who knew paper from
the city was this cool?

00:14:11.226 --> 00:14:12.560 position:50% align:center
It flies super straight!

00:14:12.644 --> 00:14:14.771 position:50% align:center
We should thank the nice lady
for giving us so much!

00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:18.525 position:50% align:center
[gasping] Those would've
been legally binding!

00:14:18.608 --> 00:14:20.151 position:50% align:center
[BOYS]
Thank you!

00:14:20.235 --> 00:14:21.528 position:50% align:center
[SELEN cries]

00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:30.829 position:50% align:center
Thanks for the underwear!
Hope you don't mind.

00:14:30.912 --> 00:14:32.872 position:50% align:center
Silly me, I didn't realize
I hadn't packed any

00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:34.374 position:50% align:center
till I jumped in the bath.

00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:37.043 position:50% align:center
Madam, it pains me to say
you have the manners of a boar.

00:14:37.127 --> 00:14:38.461 position:50% align:center
Anyone else starving?

00:14:38.545 --> 00:14:39.546 position:50% align:center
I'm famished.

00:14:39.629 --> 00:14:41.256 position:50% align:center
A post-combat appetite
is only natural,

00:14:41.339 --> 00:14:43.341 position:50% align:center
but after the ringer I've been
put through all afternoon,

00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:44.676 position:50% align:center
I could eat a house.

00:14:44.759 --> 00:14:46.594 position:50% align:center
Yeah, sorry I only had
time to cover the basics.

00:14:46.678 --> 00:14:48.722 position:50% align:center
I'm not as young
as I used to be.

00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:49.973 position:50% align:center
--Huh?
--Give me a little bit

00:14:50.056 --> 00:14:51.683 position:50% align:center
to loosen up and I'll
have you at intermediate

00:14:51.766 --> 00:14:54.269 position:50% align:center
before you can uproot a tree.

00:14:54.352 --> 00:14:56.688 position:50% align:center
[PHYLLO]
Excuse me. Do you mean...

00:14:56.771 --> 00:14:59.691 position:50% align:center
...all of that... was....

00:14:59.774 --> 00:15:02.318 position:50% align:center
...basic?!

00:15:02.402 --> 00:15:06.656 position:50% align:center
I don't remember Phyllo
being this big of a mope.

00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:10.410 position:50% align:center
Alrighty. I think the time
has come for a toast!

00:15:10.493 --> 00:15:12.287 position:50% align:center
My most heartfelt thanks.

00:15:12.370 --> 00:15:14.247 position:50% align:center
For gathering at
this festive banquet

00:15:14.330 --> 00:15:16.249 position:50% align:center
to celebrate Lloyd and I
in matrimony.

00:15:16.332 --> 00:15:17.417 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Huh?

00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:18.752 position:50% align:center
[LLOYD chuckles nervously]

00:15:18.835 --> 00:15:20.128 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS grumbling]

00:15:20.211 --> 00:15:22.047 position:50% align:center
You'll have to excuse
the chief's sense of humor.

00:15:22.130 --> 00:15:23.548 position:50% align:center
She needs to get new material.

00:15:23.631 --> 00:15:24.466 position:50% align:center
It wasn't a bit!

00:15:24.549 --> 00:15:26.926 position:50% align:center
Uh, let's try a
different toast.

00:15:27.010 --> 00:15:30.180 position:50% align:center
To my grandson, Lloyd, who's
come home a soldier.

00:15:30.263 --> 00:15:33.141 position:50% align:center
And the steadfast friends
he brought to our table!

00:15:33.224 --> 00:15:34.225 position:50% align:center
Be well!

00:15:34.309 --> 00:15:36.436 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Be well!

00:15:36.519 --> 00:15:39.022 position:50% align:center
You may now stuff your faces.

00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:40.774 position:50% align:center
This is delicious, Merthophan!

00:15:40.857 --> 00:15:42.275 position:50% align:center
Why thank you!

00:15:42.359 --> 00:15:45.528 position:50% align:center
Locally sourced gizzard of
basilisk is good for the heart.

00:15:46.905 --> 00:15:48.823 position:50% align:center
So good! So fluffy!

00:15:48.907 --> 00:15:50.492 position:50% align:center
Right? And I love the sauce!

00:15:50.575 --> 00:15:51.618 position:50% align:center
Hearty, isn't it?

00:15:51.701 --> 00:15:53.828 position:50% align:center
Roasted onion
and seafood medley.

00:15:53.912 --> 00:15:57.123 position:50% align:center
I made the sauce by steeping
a live Kraken in bone broth.

00:15:57.207 --> 00:15:59.751 position:50% align:center
[MERTHOPHAN yelling]

00:15:59.834 --> 00:16:01.586 position:50% align:center
Yeah, little guy
put up quite a fight!

00:16:01.670 --> 00:16:03.004 position:50% align:center
Oh, and the salad is made of

00:16:03.088 --> 00:16:05.090 position:50% align:center
freshly chopped
cursed sweet peppers!

00:16:05.173 --> 00:16:06.383 position:50% align:center
[CURSED PEPPERS cackling]

00:16:06.466 --> 00:16:07.801 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Okay, then.

00:16:07.884 --> 00:16:10.595 position:50% align:center
Ah! Those smiles indicate
peak freshness.

00:16:10.679 --> 00:16:11.763 position:50% align:center
[CURSED PEPPERS screaming]

00:16:11.846 --> 00:16:13.515 position:50% align:center
Yes! Love that crunch!

00:16:13.598 --> 00:16:17.310 position:50% align:center
Is any part of this feast
not comprised of monsters?

00:16:21.898 --> 00:16:23.858 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Thank you for the meal!

00:16:23.942 --> 00:16:25.985 position:50% align:center
Why don't I get started
on the cleanup?

00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:27.362 position:50% align:center
Sure! I can help you out.

00:16:27.445 --> 00:16:28.613 position:50% align:center
Oh, there's no need, dear.

00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:30.865 position:50% align:center
Nonsense, least I could
do is lend you a hand.

00:16:30.949 --> 00:16:33.743 position:50% align:center
Oh, very well, since you insist.
Thank you very much.

00:16:33.827 --> 00:16:36.705 position:50% align:center
[RIHO humming]

00:16:36.788 --> 00:16:37.997 position:50% align:center
[SELEN]
Suck up.

00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:39.916 position:50% align:center
[PHYLLO] She's just trying
to score some gold.

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:42.293 position:50% align:center
[EUG]
Heh. That Riho is goin' places.

00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:43.294 position:50% align:center
[SELEN, PHYLLO]
Huh...?

00:16:43.378 --> 00:16:45.797 position:50% align:center
Grit, curiosity,
and raw ambition.

00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:48.174 position:50% align:center
If you ask me, even if this
is all for the off chance

00:16:48.258 --> 00:16:51.344 position:50% align:center
of scoring some gold,
it's impressive.

00:16:53.138 --> 00:16:54.681 position:50% align:center
[GLUCO]
Time we blast off!

00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:56.975 position:50% align:center
[LOCOMO]
So nice to meet y'all.

00:16:57.058 --> 00:16:59.185 position:50% align:center
Thanks for coming out
and having dinner with us.

00:16:59.269 --> 00:17:00.437 position:50% align:center
I meant to ask you, Lloyd,

00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:01.938 position:50% align:center
which one of these
charming young women

00:17:02.022 --> 00:17:03.440 position:50% align:center
are you going steady with?

00:17:03.523 --> 00:17:04.524 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:06.234 position:50% align:center
Oh, it's nothing
like that, Aunt Sofra!

00:17:06.317 --> 00:17:08.445 position:50% align:center
They're just my friends
from the military academy!

00:17:08.528 --> 00:17:11.322 position:50% align:center
I have to say that's a shame.
We've been waiting all night

00:17:11.406 --> 00:17:13.158 position:50% align:center
for you to introduce us
to "the one."

00:17:13.241 --> 00:17:15.326 position:50% align:center
You're not the runt of
the litter anymore, kid.

00:17:15.410 --> 00:17:18.038 position:50% align:center
Think it's time to start taking
an interest in certain things.

00:17:18.121 --> 00:17:19.914 position:50% align:center
You gotta be sweet on somebody.

00:17:19.998 --> 00:17:21.916 position:50% align:center
[LLOYD] Come on, guys.
Knock it off, please?

00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:23.793 position:50% align:center
Well, for what my
opinion may be worth,

00:17:23.877 --> 00:17:25.712 position:50% align:center
I highly recommend Miss Riho.

00:17:25.795 --> 00:17:26.755 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Oh?

00:17:26.838 --> 00:17:28.089 position:50% align:center
[RIHO gasping]

00:17:28.173 --> 00:17:29.841 position:50% align:center
[KALOCON] She never misses
an opportunity to help.

00:17:29.924 --> 00:17:31.676 position:50% align:center
That's quality
relationship material.

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:34.721 position:50% align:center
[KOUJI] I agree. Gal's a
credit to her generation.

00:17:34.804 --> 00:17:38.600 position:50% align:center
Sure she's nice,
but my vote goes to Phyllo.

00:17:38.683 --> 00:17:40.852 position:50% align:center
She's honest, and she knows
how to handle herself.

00:17:40.935 --> 00:17:44.314 position:50% align:center
There are great things in store
for her, mark my words.

00:17:44.397 --> 00:17:46.733 position:50% align:center
Yes? And?

00:17:46.816 --> 00:17:49.778 position:50% align:center
[RIHO]
How the hell did we end up here?

00:17:49.861 --> 00:17:52.113 position:50% align:center
[PHYLLO] Pyrid backs me up,
which if you break it down

00:17:52.197 --> 00:17:53.323 position:50% align:center
is basically the same thing

00:17:53.406 --> 00:17:55.450 position:50% align:center
as getting approval
from Lloyd's parents.

00:17:55.533 --> 00:17:56.951 position:50% align:center
I'm in.

00:17:57.035 --> 00:18:00.372 position:50% align:center
Ugh! Everyone go home! No more
talk of Lloyd's love life!

00:18:00.455 --> 00:18:03.083 position:50% align:center
[SELEN screams]
Where was I when everyone else

00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:05.293 position:50% align:center
was scoring all the points?
Help me Vritra!

00:18:05.377 --> 00:18:07.295 position:50% align:center
If I don't do something to earn
their respect right now,

00:18:07.379 --> 00:18:09.798 position:50% align:center
I'll be completely out
of the running!

00:18:09.881 --> 00:18:12.384 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA]
Hmm. Okay, hear me out.

00:18:12.467 --> 00:18:14.969 position:50% align:center
Kids are wild about
the magical girl trope, right?

00:18:15.053 --> 00:18:18.181 position:50% align:center
Why not endear yourself to them
by branding me as your familiar?

00:18:18.264 --> 00:18:20.684 position:50% align:center
That's too clichÃ© to fly
with a crowd like this!

00:18:20.767 --> 00:18:22.519 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA] Really?
When my kids were younger

00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:23.728 position:50% align:center
they couldn't get
enough of that stuff.

00:18:23.812 --> 00:18:25.438 position:50% align:center
Especially the sidekicks.

00:18:25.522 --> 00:18:27.440 position:50% align:center
[EUG]
We talking magical girls?

00:18:27.524 --> 00:18:30.443 position:50% align:center
'Cause you certainly have
my attention, Princess.

00:18:30.527 --> 00:18:33.363 position:50% align:center
But I propose we take some risks
and maybe give you a sidekick

00:18:33.446 --> 00:18:35.824 position:50% align:center
a little less on-brand.
Think handsome, en flique.

00:18:35.907 --> 00:18:37.909 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA]
Hm? Handsome?

00:18:37.992 --> 00:18:40.954 position:50% align:center
[EUG] Boo-ya! I give you
Vritra's new form!

00:18:41.037 --> 00:18:43.415 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA] I look like a frog!

00:18:45.667 --> 00:18:48.795 position:50% align:center
[EUG] By the way,
I'm guessing you saw him.

00:18:48.878 --> 00:18:49.963 position:50% align:center
What's he up to?

00:18:50.046 --> 00:18:51.673 position:50% align:center
[ALKA] Nothing good,
I can tell you that.

00:18:51.756 --> 00:18:53.508 position:50% align:center
He's bent on releasing
the demon lords

00:18:53.591 --> 00:18:56.011 position:50% align:center
for some nefarious purpose.

00:18:57.595 --> 00:19:01.725 position:50% align:center
No kidding? Then maybe it's
time to take the next step.

00:19:01.808 --> 00:19:05.687 position:50% align:center
Don't let him goad us
into moving prematurely.

00:19:05.770 --> 00:19:08.690 position:50% align:center
[EUG] They've put magic
under the microscope.

00:19:08.773 --> 00:19:12.027 position:50% align:center
Some humans are even on the
verge of comprehending runes.

00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:14.738 position:50% align:center
Guesswork is no basis
on which to act.

00:19:14.821 --> 00:19:18.491 position:50% align:center
I really don't care to risk
a repeat of last time.

00:19:24.414 --> 00:19:28.376 position:50% align:center
[EUG] Vritra's memories almost
came flooding back.

00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:30.253 position:50% align:center
Imagine how he would feel.

00:19:30.337 --> 00:19:31.838 position:50% align:center
What frightful things
might he do

00:19:31.921 --> 00:19:34.466 position:50% align:center
in the throes of recollection?

00:19:34.549 --> 00:19:36.009 position:50% align:center
[ALKA]
Indeed.

00:19:37.761 --> 00:19:41.181 position:50% align:center
[ALKA]
All the same, I'd like to wait.

00:19:41.264 --> 00:19:43.516 position:50% align:center
[EUG]
It's been long enough.

00:19:44.934 --> 00:19:46.811 position:50% align:center
[VRITRA snoring]

